Police in King Williams Town arrested more than 50 suspects, aged between 19 and 58 years-old, for various crimes over the weekend. According to police spokesperson, Captain Siphokazi Mawisa, police were conducting a weekend operation up until Monday morning - tracking down suspects and also doing crime prevention duties in ensuring that citizens are safe and secured. They managed to arrest these suspects for crimes ranging from, Drunken driving, possession of stolen property, possession of drugs, common robbery, theft, murder, common assault, drunkenness, housebreaking and theft, said Captain Mawisa.She added that police also confiscated dangerous weapons while they were doing stop and search operations. Illegal liquor outlets were closed and dangerous weapons and recovered stolen goods were confiscated by police during the operation, she added.Captain Mawisa said that police also followed up on the information they received after a business robbery that occurred at a spaza shop at Zwelitsha, King Williams s town, over the weekend. They managed to arrest four suspects and recovered a firearm and goods that were stolen from the local schools and business place in their policing precinct, she said.The suspects appeared at different Magistrate's Courts around King Williams Town on Monday and Tuesday.King William s Town Cluster Commander, Brigadier Luntu Ngubelanga, said that police commended the members for a job well done over the past weekend. He also thanked the community for sharing valuable information to the police that led to the arrest of suspects. We will ensure that all perpetrators of crime are brought before court, added Brigadier Ngubelanga.He also encouraged the community members to report any criminal activities to 08600 10111 or their nearest Police Station. 